def get_total_cost(df, unit=0):
    #   
    df["total_cost"] = df["end_balance"] * df["unit_cost"]

    #   
    df = df[["warehouse_id", "unit_id", "date", "total_cost"]]

    #      
    df = (
        df.sort_values(by="date")
        .groupby(["warehouse_id", "unit_id", "date"], as_index=False)["total_cost"]
        .last()
    )

    #  
    if unit:
        df = df[df["unit_id"] == unit]

    #   ,  
    df = df.groupby(["warehouse_id", "date"], as_index=False)["total_cost"].sum()

    #  
    df.date = pd.to_datetime(df.date)

    #    
    dates = pd.DataFrame(
        pd.date_range(start="2016-01-01", end="2024-09-30", freq="D"), columns=["date"]
    )

    #    
    df = dates.merge(df, on="date", how="left")

    #   
    result = (
        df.pivot(index="date", columns="warehouse_id", values="total_cost")
        .dropna(how="all", axis=1)
        .ffill(axis=0)
    )

    #    
    result["total"] = result.sum(axis=1)

    return result

def get_cumcost_shipped(df, unit=0):
    #      
    df = df[(~df.not_valuable_send) & (df.outcome > 0)]

    #      
    if unit:
        df = df[df["unit_id"] == unit]

    #    
    df = df[["unit_id", "date", "outcome", "unit_cost"]]

    #   
    df["total_cost"] = df["outcome"] * df["unit_cost"]

    #  
    df.date = pd.to_datetime(df.date)

    #    
    dates = pd.DataFrame(
        pd.date_range(start="2016-01-01", end="2024-09-30", freq="D"), columns=["date"]
    )

    #    
    df = dates.merge(df, on="date", how="left")

    #   
    result = df.fillna(0).groupby("date")["total_cost"].sum().cumsum(axis=0)

    return result

def get_cumcost_stored(df, unit=0):
    #  
    if unit:
        df = df[df["unit_id"] == unit]

    #   
    df = df[["date", "end_balance", "cost_per_day"]]

    #   
    df["store_total_cost"] = df["end_balance"] * df["cost_per_day"]

    #  
    df.date = pd.to_datetime(df.date)

    #        
    df = df.groupby("date", as_index=False)["store_total_cost"].sum()

    #    
    dates = pd.DataFrame(
        pd.date_range(start="2016-01-01", end="2024-09-30", freq="D"), columns=["date"]
    )

    #    
    df = dates.merge(df, on="date", how="left").set_index("date")

    #      
    df = df.ffill(axis=0).fillna(0)

    #   
    result = df.cumsum(axis=0)

    return result

In[264]:
def get_cost_stored_with_illiquid(df, unit=0):
    def get_valuable_date(row):
        if row["not_valuable_send"] or row["outcome"] == 0:
            return np.nan
        else:
            return row["date"]

    def is_liquid(row):
        if np.abs((row["last_shipping"] - row["date"]).days) >= 180:
            return "illiquid"
        else:
            return "liquid"

    #  
    if unit:
        df = df[df["unit_id"] == unit]

    #  ,    ,    
    df["last_shipping"] = df.apply(lambda row: get_valuable_date(row), axis=1)
    df["last_shipping"] = pd.to_datetime(df["last_shipping"])

    #   
    df = df[["date", "end_balance", "cost_per_day", "last_shipping"]]

    #   
    df["store_total_cost"] = df["end_balance"] * df["cost_per_day"]

    #  
    df.date = pd.to_datetime(df.date)

    #        
    df = df.groupby("date", as_index=False).agg(
        {"store_total_cost": "sum", "last_shipping": "first"}
    )

    #    
    dates = pd.DataFrame(
        pd.date_range(start="2016-01-01", end="2024-09-30", freq="D"), columns=["date"]
    )

    #    
    df = dates.merge(df, on="date", how="left")

    #      
    df = df.ffill(axis=0)
    df["status"] = df.apply(is_liquid, axis=1)

    #   
    df = df.pivot_table(
        index="date", columns="status", values="store_total_cost", aggfunc="sum"
    )

    if len(df.columns) == 1:
        df["illiquid"] = np.nan

    return df  # .fillna(0)

def plot_all(df, unit=0, filter=7, period=("2020-01-01", "2024-09-30")):
    plt.figure(figsize=(20, 8))

    #    
    n_3 = profiles[profiles.unit_id == unit]["volume"].min()
    n = int((n_3 ** (1 / 3)) * 100)

    plt.title(
        f'{unit}, {obor_data.loc[unit]["unit_name"]}\nA:   {obor_data.loc[unit]["unit_art"]}\n:     {obor_data.loc[unit]["unit_brand"]}\n:     {n_3:.2f} 3.    ({n}x{n}x{n} .)',
        loc="left",
    )
    # plt.gcf().set_facecolor('#ECDFCC')
    # plt.gca().set_facecolor('#FCFAEE')

    #   
    plt.step(
        x=get_cumcost_shipped(df, unit).index,
        y=get_cumcost_shipped(df, unit),
        where="post",
        color="#A5B68D",
        linewidth=5,
    )

    plt.step(
        x=get_cumcost_stored(df, unit).index,
        y=get_cumcost_stored(df, unit),
        where="post",
        color="#DA8359",
        linewidth=5,
    )

    plt.step(
        x=get_total_cost(df, unit).index,
        y=(
            get_total_cost(df, unit)
            .melt(ignore_index=False)
            .reset_index()
            .groupby("date")
            .value.sum()
            .rolling(filter)
            .mean()
        ),
        where="post",
        linestyle="--",
        color="#BC9F8B",
        linewidth=2,
    )

    plt.grid()
    plt.gca().set_yticklabels(
        ["{:,.0f}".format(y).replace(",", " ") for y in plt.gca().get_yticks()]
    )
    plt.xlim(pd.to_datetime(period[0]), pd.to_datetime(period[1]))
    plt.legend(
        [" ", "  ", "  "]
    )
    plt.show()

def plot_metric(df, unit=0, filter=7, period=("2020-01-01", "2024-09-30")):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5), dpi=100)

    dfs = get_cumcost_stored(df, unit).merge(
        get_cumcost_shipped(df, unit), on="date", how="outer"
    )
    dfs["metric"] = (dfs["total_cost"] - dfs["store_total_cost"]) / dfs["total_cost"]

    plt.step(x=dfs.index, y=dfs["metric"], where="post", color="blue", linewidth=2)

    if unit:
        plt.title(f'{unit}, {obor_data.loc[unit]["unit_name"]}')
    else:
        plt.title(f"All")
    plt.grid()
    plt.gca().set_yticklabels(
        ["{:,.0f}".format(y).replace(",", " ") for y in plt.gca().get_yticks()]
    )
    plt.xlim(pd.to_datetime(period[0]), pd.to_datetime(period[1]))
    # plt.ylim(-2, 2)
    plt.legend(
        [
            "  ",
            "  ",
            "  ",
        ]
    )
    plt.show()

In[183]:
metrics_data = []

for unit in df.unit_id.unique():
    #       
    df_metric = get_cumcost_stored(df, unit).merge(
        get_cumcost_shipped(df, unit), on="date", how="outer"
    )

    #       
    df_metric = df_metric.merge(
        get_total_cost(df, unit)[["total"]], on="date", how="outer"
    )

    #   
    df_metric["kpi"] = df_metric["store_total_cost"] / (
        df_metric["total_cost"] + df_metric["total"]
    )

    #   
    metrics_data.append(
        {
            "unit_id": unit,
            "kpi": df_metric.loc[df_metric.index.max()]["kpi"],
            "date": df_metric.index.max(),
            "storage_value": df_metric.loc[df_metric.index.max()]["store_total_cost"],
            "shipping_value": df_metric.loc[df_metric.index.max()]["total_cost"],
            "balance_value": df_metric.loc[df_metric.index.max()]["total"],
            "storage_value_last_month": df_metric.loc[df_metric.index.max()][
                "store_total_cost"
            ]
            - df_metric.loc[df_metric.index.max() - pd.Timedelta(30, "day")][
                "store_total_cost"
            ],
        }
    )

metrics_data = pd.DataFrame(metrics_data)

metrics_data.head().style.format(
    {
        "kpi": "{:.2%}",
        "storage_value": " {:.2f}",
        "shipping_value": " {:.2f}",
        "balance_value": " {:.2f}",
        "storage_value_last_month": " {:.2f}",
    }
)

def evaluate_losses(row, filter_ratio=0.015):
    filter_value = row["balance_value"] + row["shipping_value"] * filter_ratio
    loss = row["storage_value"] - filter_value
    if loss > 0:
        return loss
    else:
        return 0
